    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-10-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-10-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="527"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/1379a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-09T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 9, 1928—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>343. Your despatch 1614, August 15. Referring to last paragraph the Department
                    authorizes you singly or jointly with interested colleagues to file general
                    notification of outstanding obligations of China to American citizens in general
                    accord with the memorandum enclosed with the Legation’s despatch of March 25,
                        1926.<note n="2" xml:id="d527fn2">Despatch not printed. For text of its
                        enclosure, see memorandum of Mar. 18, 1926, from the American, British,
                        French, and Japanese Ministers to the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs,
                            <ref target="frus1926v01#pg_947">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1926, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 947</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
